VMware Secure State App for Splunk README
Please refer to the VMware Documentation site to get started with using the Splunk app.
https://docs.securestate.vmware.com/

Requirements
- Python 3.5 or greater
- Pip (Python package manager) https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/installing/
- Python Requests Library https://pypi.org/project/requests/

Setup Instructions
- After installation, ensure that the VMware Secure State app appears in the list of apps and add-ons.
- Create a new index called "vss" with the default settings.
- In the _json SourceType, change the Timestamp field to "creationTime".
    This can be done by going to the advanced section in the  _json SourceType and entering creationTime as the value in the "Timestamp fields".
- Find the csp-token.txt file in the vss-splunk-app/bin folder and replace your CSP token in there. (Optional)
- Run the vss4.py file to generate findings, rules, and compliance info using the command:
    If you placed your token in the csp-token.txt file, use the command:
    python3 vss4.py
    Or run the script providing your CSP token inline:
    python3 vss4.py -t TOKEN_VALUE
- If you see any errors, make sure you have the requirements listed above.
- Verify that new json files are created in the vss-splunk-app/bin/data folder.
- Go to the VSS Splunk app dashboard, and you should see all the dashboards displaying your security data now.

For any questions or comments, please send an email to: vss-splunk@vmware.com
